# Trivy IaC / vuln scan suppressions for Glad-Labs/poindexter.
#
# Each entry must include a rationale comment. CI policy: suppression
# without explanation is grounds for revert.

# DS-0002 — "Specify at least 1 USER command in Dockerfile with non-root user"
#
# Container images that legitimately run as root in this stack:
#
#   scripts/Dockerfile.voice-agent
#     Spawns `claude` (Claude Code CLI) as a subprocess, which reads
#     ~/.claude bind-mounted READ-WRITE from the host. Switching the
#     in-container user breaks host-side ownership of the cached
#     session JSONLs and the per-call --session-id resume flow.
#     Hardening tracked separately as a per-component split
#     (Glad-Labs/poindexter#432).
#
#   scripts/Dockerfile.backup
#     Alpine + postgresql-client running pg_dump against the brain
#     volume. The dump writes into a bind-mounted host directory; the
#     host UID alignment is messy on Windows-Docker-Desktop, and
#     dropping privileges makes the bind-mount unwritable. The image
#     surface is tiny (no Python, no app code), which limits the
#     blast radius.
#
#   scripts/Dockerfile.gpu-exporter
#     Reads /proc/driver/nvidia (driver-owned). Dropping privileges
#     requires fiddling with the nvidia-smi capability model that
#     isn't worth it for a low-value metric exporter.
#
#   scripts/Dockerfile.auto-embed
#     Phase-B one-shot job — runs to completion, exits, container
#     destroyed. Not a persistent attack surface.
#
# scripts/Dockerfile.voice-bot, scripts/Dockerfile.sdxl, and
# scripts/Dockerfile.wan already have USER directives and DO NOT
# rely on this suppression.
DS-0002
